  "text": "In [CITATION_1] , we proposed green scheduling as an approach to reduce the peak demand by coordinating the heaters so that at any time, at most k of them, for 1 ≤ k ≤ n, can be on simultaneously while maintaining thermal comfort. The results were obtained for systems with no interaction between zones (K ij = 0), no internal heat gain (d i = 0), and a constant global ambient air temperature (T a,i = T a = const). In this paper, we remove those restrictions and derive a schedulability condition for the system as well as a scalable method for synthesizing periodic schedules.",
